::Whistler::
       "That's okay last time I was here this was a ship not a city.  I 
nearly died protecting their leader.  I woke up in a city.  Go figure."  He 
grimaced.  "Then there was a big beam that blasted the hell out of it and I 
flew into a tree and nearly died again."  He looks around in mock concern.  
"I'm sorry, do I sound bitter?"  As if remembering something he puts his hand 
up.  "Oh and before both of those I was at a different ship that got blown 
up.  And I ended up in the bushes half dead.  But maybe I'm just a bit jaded."


--part1_ba.20419de7.2984a8e6_boundary
